-- Baywa Considers Grain Trade Acquisitions, FAZ Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-03-23T08:10:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/baywa-considers-grain-trade-acquisitions-faz-reports.html
Baywa AG (BYW6)  is looking at takeovers in
the grain trade, to broaden its international reach, the
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, citing an interview
with Chief Executive Officer Klaus Josef Lutz.  While Lutz declined to name any potential takeover targets,
he said Baywa is “working on one concrete option,” according
to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt at 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
